.SH NAME
dotty-env-remove - Remove credentials from a namespace.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty env remove [] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove one credential by KEY, the whole namespace with --all, or pick several
interactively (a filterable checklist) when no KEY is given. Removing the last
credential also removes the namespace's keychain item.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--all\fP[=false]
	remove the entire namespace

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for remove


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--namespace\fP="default"
	credential namespace to operate on

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty env remove --namespace=aws AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
  dotty env remove --namespace=aws --all
  dotty env rm --namespace=aws
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-env(1)\fP
